\end{example}

We now define the \emph{toggle poset}, which we will use in Theorem~\ref{thm:toggpstructure}.
\begin{definition}
\label{def:Lposet}
Let $E$ be a finite set, and $\mathcal{L}\subseteq 2^E$. The \emph{toggle poset} $\mathcal{P}_{\mathcal{L}}$ of $\mathcal{L}$ is defined as the partial order on $\mathcal{L}$ where the covering relations are given by $X\lessdot Y$ if and only if $X\subseteq Y$ and $|Y\setminus X|=1$, that is, if there exists $e\in E$ such that $t_e(X)=Y$. 
\end{definition}

