\section{Construction of the power set toggle group and subset-toggle groups}
\label{sec:powerset}
We now construct an even more general toggle group. Rather than defining toggles for single elements in $E$, we extend this notion to the toggle $t_S$ of a subset $S\subseteq E$.

As before, let $E$ be a countable set and $\mathcal{L}$ be any subset of the power set~$2^{E}$. 
\begin{definition}
\label{def:subsettog}
For any subset $S\subseteq E$ define its \emph{(subset-)toggle} $t_S:\mathcal{L}\rightarrow\mathcal{L}$ as

text:
\[
 t_S(X) =
  \begin{cases}
   X\triangle S & \text{if } X\triangle S\in \mathcal{L} \\
