This discussion leads us to conjecture the following strengthening of Theorem~\ref{thm:row}. 
\begin{conjecture} 
\label{conj:ccrow}
Given a finite ground set $E$ and a closure operator $\tau$ with set of closed sets $\mathcal{L}\subseteq 2^E$,
if cover-closure ${\xi}:\mathcal{L}\rightarrow\mathcal{L}$ is injective and thus bijective, then $\mathcal{L}=J(P)$ for some poset~$P$. 
\end{conjecture}

Together with Lemma~\ref{lem:ccrow}, this conjecture would imply that cover-closure ${\xi}:\mathcal{L}\rightarrow\mathcal{L}$ is bijective if and only if $\mathcal{L}=J(P)$ for some some poset~$P$.

